<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - USCS RAISED BY SALOMON.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - USCS RAISED BY SALOMON.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Salomon Brothers said on Wednesday it raised its rating on the shares of USCS International Inc to buy from hold on the belief that the recent sell-off in the stock was overdone.</p>
<p>-- &quot;USCS's stock was down 34 percent on Monday and another six percent yesterday in reaction to CSG Sytems pruchase of Tele-Communications Inc's internal billing system and processing business,&quot; analyst Richard Weingarten said in a research note. &quot;We believe this is overdone...&quot;</p>
<p>-- TCI was USCS's largest client, he said.</p>
<p>-- The stock was unchanged at 19.</p>
<p>((Wall Street desk 212-859-1730))</p>
